<section id="fs-idm255361008">
<title>Moving Up</title>
<para id="fs-idm261118720">Once you have been on the job for a while, you will want to get ahead and be promoted. <emphasis effect="bold"><link target-id="fs-idm255374112" document=""/></emphasis> offers several suggestions for improving your chances of promotion. The first item might seem a bit strange, yet it’s there for a practical reason. If you don’t really like what you do, you won’t be committed enough to compete with those who do. The passionate people are the ones who go the extra mile, do the extra work, and come up with fresh out-of-the-box ideas.</para>
<para id="fs-idm264448672">So there you have it. Remember: it’s never too early to begin planning your career—the future is now.</para>
<table id="fs-idm255374112" summary="">
